Trinijove helped 6000 people young, threatened from the social exclusion
The organization was started up to avoid the Marginalisierung by young people without professional training.
The first 25 years of the social welfare organization Trinijove led to important results: 6000 people young, threatened from the social exclusion were supported in this quarter century in order to find a way out from their difficult situation.
In addition the jobs gotten over hundred for this social group come.
On the occasion of the anniversary balance was drawn yesterday by Fabra i Coats, which more than 300 persons participated in, at an event in the former work buildings.
Trinijove was started up in 1986 in the quarter Trinitat Vella with the aim of helping young people with small training state, without work, with drug problems which were threatened from the risk of the Marginalität.
Numerous persons responsible of facilities and institutions who cooperated with the association during these 25 years participated in the celebration of yesterday in Sant Andreu.
The participation of political representatives of different directions at election campaign times proved the neutrality of the work achieved by Trinijove.
Except for the president of the Generalitat (Parliament of the Autonomous Catalonia Region), Artur Mas, and his predecessor Jordi Pujol the former socialist education minister Ernest Maragall and the former mayor took at the ceremonies and at present link-green town council Ricard Goma teil.
Also the present Catalan minister of social one and family, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the president of the public social aid of the savings bank La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa, went to the big hall of Fabra i Coats.
Mas stressed that Trinijove was started up in very difficult times and that the present times are not less complicated. But he added that the work achieved until now is a good basis.
For the president of the Generalitat Trinijove is a model, that to fight against difficult circumstances white and people in trouble gives hope.
"The depression is not anything new" for the association and the work which it achieves", it declared.
